nstruction projects, including Middle East. My expertise encompasses a wide spectrum of projects, from highrise buildings, hotels to luxury villas and residential house, commercial buildings, Accommodation with proficiency in both pre and post contract stages. I have a strong track record as a Quantity Surveyor, managing commercial aspects for international contractors and consultants. With excellent communication and problem solving skills, I am now seeking and opportunity to contribute my expertise and grow in dynamic, ambitious organization. Page 2 of 3 Duties & Responsibilities Taking off Quantities (Civil, MEP) and verifying with BOQ by using Auto CAD. Prepare and submit the interim payment Application to Consultant, Along with Necessary Supporting Document. BOQ Preparation for Sub-Contractor Works. Maintaining subcontractor in voices and certifying payments. Visit to Site for Verifying Subcontractor Work Done/Physical Measurement. Evaluating Variation or Cost submission from subcontractor in accordance with condition of contract. Review and recommendation of subcontractor claims. Preparation of cost comparison of subcontractor /supplier quotations. Review and Collect Supporting Document like WIR, MIR Working progress site photos and Shop Drawings etc for the preparation of Interim Payment Application. Evaluation and Recommendation of Sub-Contractor Payment Analysis the Changes of Drawings (Tender Vs IFC). Presence Commercial Meetings with consultant, Negotiating, Agreeing, Claim and Variations. Attend various types of Meetings (Internal and External Meetings) Such as Contractual & Progress Meeting with Consultant and Sub-Contractors. Assisting on Cost Controls and Value Engineering. Reporting to the Project Manager and Other Responsibilities.  POSITION - QUANTITY SURVEYOR (SRI LANKA)  COMPANY NAME - Engineering & Construction Solutions (Pvt) Ltd ||  PROJECT - Commercial Buildings (2B+G+5) |  PERIOD - | 2019-2020 | Luxury villas  POSITION - JR QUANTITY SURVEYOR & SITE ENGINEER (SRI LANKA)  COMPANY NAME - A.R. Architecture & Construction (pvt) Ltd ||  PROJECT - Residential House & villas (2B+G+4) |  PERIOD - | 2017-2018 | Duties & Responsibilities Quantity- Take off from the Drawings & Preparing Tender Queries. Review the Projects Drawings and Specifications. Preparation of Bill of Quantity. Requesting Quotation from Sub Contractor and Suppliers in Tender Stage and Preparation of Sub contract Document. Regular Visit to Site and Monitor Progress. Assist Senior Quantity Surveyor in the Submission of Monthly Interim Valuations. Coordinate with Project Engineers and Prepare Monthly Progress Report. Study Tender Documents (Contractual Letter, Specification, Drawing and BOQ) to identify the Scope of Work & to collect the Tender Details. Attend Meeting with Subcontractors to Finalize the Payment. Preparation of Monthly Cost Value Reconciliation and Financial Report. Prepare Variation and get Approval from Consultant Along with Necessary Supporting Documents. Site inspection Supervision, Organizing and Coordination of the Site Activities. Page 3 of 3 COMPUTER LITERACY FAMILIARIZED DOCUMENT MS Office (Excel, Word, MS Project) Standard method of measurement of Auto CAD Building Works - (SMM7) Revit Condition of contract - (FIDIC) Sketch Up New Rules of Measurement - (NRM 1&2) Plan swift Principles of Measurement International- (POMI) Internet Applications Civil Engineering Standard Method of Cost-X Measurement - (CESMM 3,4) PERSONAL PROFILE Full Name : SAMOON SABRINAS Nationality : Sri Lankan Driving License : Sri Lanka Civil Status : Single Passport Number : N9053247 Iqama Status : Transferable Iqama"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported project details","description":"Qatar Regis Hotel Ruqsha luxury house Sihan project Srilanka Commercial Build Infra Al kheesa Qatar || Luxury villas Qatar Labour Accommodation Luxury villa Srilanka Residential House Roads of infra Qatar"}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\CV- S 